cs.NI, cs.AI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.LG 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper deals with optimizing network throughput in UAV networks. 
2. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper proposes a distributed learning scheme to combat dynamic topology and varying interference. 
3. cs.IT (Information Theory) is relevant as the paper considers constraints on transmission power and quality of service (QoS). 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper proposes a game-theoretic approach to POCs assignment. 
5. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the paper introduces uncertainties and fuzzy numbers to characterize the dynamic channel gains among UAV nodes and implements the learning and decision process in a mapped fuzzy space.
